## Phase 3: The Soda & Soil Hypothesis  

This project adopts the **Soda & Soil Hypothesis** to explain modern micronutrient collapse through two reinforcing mechanisms.

### Pathway 1: Soil Depletion (FAO)  
- Intensive monocropping  
- Declining soil organic matter  
- Reduced mineral density of staple crops  

Food grown in depleted soil may deliver calories without delivering nutrients.

### Pathway 2: Processed Food Consumption  
- High sugar and phosphate intake  
- Reduced absorption of iron, calcium, and magnesium  
- Displacement of whole foods  

### Nutritional Debt  
Nutritional debt accumulates when caloric intake is maintained while micronutrient intake is chronically insufficient.  
This debt manifests later as:
- Cognitive impairment  
- Immune system dysfunction  
- Increased chronic disease risk  

